<HEADLINE> Presidential Election Starts in Lithuania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania started its
presidential election at 7:00 local time on Sunday, and 2.6
million voters were called to vote at 2,039 voting
stations nationwide, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
There are seven candidates running for the presidency,
including U.S. ecologist of Lithuanian origin Valdas Adamkus,
members of parliament Vytenis Andriukaitis, Kazys Bobelis and
Rimantas Smetona, parliament chairman Vytautas Landsbergis, Rector
of the Vilnius University Rolandas Pavilionis and
ex-prosecutor-general Arturas Paulauskas.
</P>
<P>
The current 65-year old president Algirdas Brazauskas has
refused to run for a second term.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary results showed only about 7.22 percent voters
went to the polls by 10:00 local time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
