<HEADLINE> Zambia's Most Parties to Attend Inter-Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Zambian's most parties have
confirmed the attendance at the inter-party dialogue scheduled next
month to discuss the contentious issues facing the country, a
high-ranking ruling party official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Micheal Sata, National Secretary of the Ruling Movement for the
Multi-party Democracy (MMD) and government Minister Withou Portfolio,
said that 28 political parties have so far registered for the dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 31 parties which attended the preliminary meeting early
this month and drew an agenda for the inter-party dialogue, only three
have not yet registered, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sata, who is co-chairman of the preliminary meeting, said
preparations for the meeting have reached an advanced stage and the
MMD will not accept any new proposals from the opposition.
</P>
<P>
The dialogue to be attended by party presidents will follow the
agenda, which includes most contentious issues like constitution,
electoral process and voters' register and fresh registration, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Sata said president frederick Chiluba is very keen over the
dialogue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
