establish Africa as a continent free from "perennial" conflicts,
displaced people, refugees and political and economic woes.
</P>
<P>
Kagame described his visit as "fruitful", saying that the
visit has provided him an opportunity to strengthen the
cooperation between Rwanda and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the potential for trade and economic are
"tremendous".
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan vice-president, heading a 15-member delegaiton,
arrived in Zambia Thursday on a three-day visit. 
