<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian President Meets Chinese Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad met here today with visiting Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen to discuss the Mideast peace process
and bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian president welcomed Qian's visit to Syria, saying
that relations between the two countries are firm. Syria, he said,
adheres to the ties of friendship with China under all conditions,
expressing the hope that these relations will undergo further
development.
</P>
<P>
Al-Assad reaffirmed Syria's adherence to the Mideast peace
process as a strategic option. He expressed Syria's desire to
reach a just and comprehensive regional settlement through
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
He said that while the international community sought peace in
the Middle East region, "the Israeli government ignores this
desire."
</P>
<P>
On his part, Qian said that "we appreciate Syria's pursuit of a
policy of independence and non-alignment and the safeguarding of
the just interests of Arab states and the Palestinian people."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister said that there could be no
settlement of the Arab-Israeli conflict without Syria's
participation.
</P>
<P>
China supports Syria's call for the resumption of negotiations
along the Syrian-Israeli track from the point they have reached
before suspension, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Golan Heights, he added, are indivisible part of the Syrian
territories, and China supports all Syrian efforts to restore the
Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the land-for-peace is the basis for resolving the
Middle East problem. It conforms with the U.N. Security Council
resolutions, and should constitute the grounds for the
establishment of just and comprehensive peace in the region, he
said.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Qian said the bonds of friendship and
cooperation between China and Syria have undergone satisfactory
development since the two countries established diplomatic
relations in 1956.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and people highly esteem the existing
friendship between the two countries and wish to further develop
these cordial relations under the new situation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian also met with Syrian Prime Minister Mahmoud Zouebi today.
</P>
<P>
Qian arrived here Saturday for a two-day official visit to
Syria, the second leg of his Mideast tour which has taken him to
Lebanon and will also take him to Israel, the Palestinian
self-rule areas and Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
