<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Speaker Slams Israeli Proposed Pullback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Council Speaker
Ahmed Qureia today blasted Israel's proposed troop pullback in the
West Bank as an attempt to kill the peace process before the final
status talks begin.
</P>
<P>
Qureia, also known as Abu Ala, said that signed agreements
demand Israel withdraw from 62 percent of the West Bank in three
successive phases in addition to 28 percent of the lands Israel
has handed over to the Palestinian National Authority (PNA),
Palestinian Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that only the remaining 10 percent of the West
Bank will be reserved for the final status negotiations.
</P>
<P>
He added that the "logic of the agreements is clear that the
Israelis will redeploy from all of the Palestinian lands occupied
in 1967, including East Jerusalem."
</P>
<P>
Qureia was commenting on media reports that Israel's cabinet is
discussing several maps that outline the percentage of its
proposed withdrawal and guidelines for the final settlement.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu reportedly has
prepared to hand over to the Palestinians about 10 percent of the
West Bank in the second of the three-phase redeployments.
</P>
<P>
He has urged the PNA to accept his proposal that the last
redeployment be included in the final status talks, which have
been scheduled to settle the thorniest issues of Jerusalem, final
borders and Palestinian refugees according to signed accords.
</P>
<P>
Under the plans the Israeli cabinet is discussing, Israel will
agree to hand over altogether about 30-50 percent of the West Bank
to the PNA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971222.0022 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-21 19:51 </DATE_TIME>
