<HEADLINE> UAE Welcomes Iran's Positive Attitude toward </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates
(UAE) today welcome Iran's recent rapprochement attitude to their
territory disputes, but demanded Iran take actions, the Kuwaiti
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"We share the Gulf's positive reaction to recent Iranian
statements... but the United Arab Emirates hopes that the
Iranian leadership translates its statements into actions," UAE
Minister of Information and Culture Sheikh Abdullah bin Zayed
Al-Nahyan told the agency.
</P>
<P>
Iran recently repeated its readiness to improve relations with
the Gulf Arab countries. Iranian President Mohammad Khatami said
last week that he is willing to go to the UAE to discuss the issue
of the three islands of Greater Tunb, lesser Tunb and Abu Musa.
</P>
<P>
Both the UAE and Iran claim sovereignty over the islands.
</P>
<P>
The UAE and the other members of the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) have called on Tehran to resolve the disputes through
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Abdullah said his country wants Iran to "respond to
repeated calls to resolve the issue of Iran's occupation of the
three islands through peaceful means."
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the six GCC Arab states of Kuwait, the UAE,
Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Qatar and Oman started Saturday the
three-day GCC summit in Kuwait. 
</P>
</TEXT>
