<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1400 GMT, December 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Chechen fighters attacked the city of Buynaksk in the
southern Russian republic of Dagestan early Monday morning,
causing several casualties, burning four tanks and vehicles and
taking nine hostages away to Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Russian media reported that about 30 fighters armed with
machine-guns and rocket-launchers attacked a Russian tank
battalion stationed in Buynaksk.
</P>
<P>
During the two-hour volley of gunfire, two tanks, two fuel
trucks and three military trucks were burned down. One civilian
was killed and five people injured. (Russia-Chechnya-Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- Britain, Germany, Italy and Spain signed an accord here
Monday formally confirming their participation in the costly
project to build a 21st-century warplane for Europe.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord signed by German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe and
his counterparts from Britain, George Robertson, Italy, Beniamino
Andreatta and Spain, Eduardo Serra, a total of 620 Eurofighter jets
will be built and delivered to the four nations between 2002 and 2014.
</P>
<P>
Britain is buying 232 Eurofighters, Germany 180, Italy 121 and
Spain 87. The total cost of the project is estimated at up to 65
billion dollars. (German-Eurofighter)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Lithuanian presidential elections ended with no final
results because none of the seven candidates got more than 50
percent of the votes.
</P>
<P>
Former Prosecutor-General Arturas Paulauskas with 42.5 percent
of votes took the lead in the elections on Sunday, the Itar-Tass
news agency reported from Vilnius.
</P>
<P>
Paulauskas, 44, is followed by Valdas Adamkus, a 71-year-old
American ecologist of Lithuanian descent, who got 28.2 percent of
the ballots. (Lithuania-Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Vietnam detected 1,400 cases of smuggling and trade
fraudulence, and handled illegal imports worth 62 billion
vietnamese dong ( 4.7 million U.S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
These were achieved over one month of implementation of the
national anti-smuggling and trade fraudulence
campaign. (Vietnam-Anti-Smuggling)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- Seven members of the international environmental group
Greenpeace early Monday blocked a ferry at the northern German
port of Bremerhaven, which was due to ship plutonium to Scotland
for reprocessing.
</P>
<P>
With soldering irons, they attached themselves to the exit ramp
of the ferry Arneb. Port police later came trying to remove the
demonstrators, who also employed three rubber dinghies in the
blockade. (Germany-Greenpeace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- A local hunger relief organization in California
opened more food pantry distribution sites to meet the needs of
thousands of Californians who worry about their next meal.
</P>
<P>
In San Francisco alone, more than 90,000 people, including
20,000 infants, children and adolescents, live at or below the
poverty line. That means one in 10 adults and one in five children
regularly go hungary, said a report by the local Food Bank.
</P>
<P>
While the federal government's poverty line for a family of
three is 13,500 U.S. dollars, a family of three with one wage
earner and two children needs an income of 36,000 dollars to live
a decent life in San Francisco. (California-Food-Distribution)
</P>
