<HEADLINE> 1551 Militants Killed in Turkey Since June: Senior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Interior Minister
Murat Basesgioglu said here today that 1551 militants have been
killed since the formation of the new government at the end of
June this year.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted Basesgioglu as
saying that 264 soldiers and nine officers of the Turkish
security forces were also killed in the operations against
anti-government rebels during the period.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that 84 civilians also lost their lives. He
said that 554 soldiers and 286 rebels were wounded during this
period.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish security forces have been launching strong military
operations against the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in
southeastern and northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war in
southeastern Turkey for autonomy since August 1984. 
</P>
