<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists, Technicians Honored at Awards Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese scientist who
designed a bulletproof car once used by President Richard Nixon
during his 1972 China visit was one of the 291 scientists and
technicians to be given awards today.
</P>
<P>
Xu Xingyao and the other recipients were selected from a large
field of about 20 million Chinese scientists and technicians. They
included Lin Yuanpei, the designer of Shanghai's Yangpu Bridge,
which has the world's longest cable-stay span, and Gao Dengyi, the
first Chinese to do scientific studies at the North and South
Poles and on the Qinghai-Tibetan Plateau.
</P>
<P>
The biennial ceremony was established by the China Association
for Science and Technology (CAST) with the idea of encouraging
scientists and technicians who have made great contributions,
especially those who have worked in remote or impoverished areas
for years.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yutai, a CAST official, said that winners are not judged
on their achievements alone, but on their moral character and
spirit of giving as well. 
</P>
