<HEADLINE> East Coast Harbor Is China's Second Largest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao Harbor, in China's
Shandong Province, has become the country's second largest port,
after Shanghai, and till today, has handled more than a million
TEUs (twenty-foot equivalent units).
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the harbor was completed today, two years
ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
It has got 300 million yuan (36 million US dollars) to
improve its facilities and rebuild its large deep-draft
berths. The new and old harbor areas combined cover a
1.5-million-sq.m. area.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of construction was the only harbor
construction project approved by the State Council in 1995 and was
the first key state construction project to be completed in
1997-2000.
</P>
<P>
The project cost at least 1.57 billion yuan for six deep-draft
berths and multi-purpose berths, which will add 5.1 million tons
of freight handling capacity to the harbor.  
</P>
</TEXT>
