<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls For Cohesiveness of Party Leading Bodies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, General Secretary
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, today
called for greater cohesiveness and better work efficiency of the
Party leading bodies at all levels.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national meeting on Party organization work today,
he said that in implementing the principle of democratic
centralism earnestly, "we must improve the system of combining the
collective leadership with the division of work with individual
responsibility."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the 21st century will be one full of
opportunities and challenges and to face the coming new century,
"thousands of senior leading officials and tens of thousands of
middle ranking leading officials should shoulder the important
historic tasks ahead."
</P>
<P>
During the century, the Party will lead the Chinese people to
achieve the all-round revitalization of the Chinese nation, he
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
To do so, he said, they need to have the guidance of correct
theory and political line, the unity and hard work of the whole
nation, and the strong leadership by the Party organizations at
all levels.
</P>
<P>
Among these conditions, he stressed, the leading officials are
"an important and decisive factor."
</P>
<P>
Leading officials need to be bold and resolute and especially
need to have an overall view and democratic style, and need to
learn to respect other people and draw on collective wisdom and
absorb all useful ideas, he added.
</P>
<P>
"All important decisions must be made through collective
discussions," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The whole situation has been considered, all important Central
Committee decisions have been made, and plans have been drawn up
based on research and opinions gathered from all over, he said,
and now, Party organizations and all departments need to put these
into effect.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also asked Party organizations and government to show
concern for laid-off workers and people living in
disaster-stricken areas to make sure that they have a joyful Lunar
New Year next month.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders present at the meeting were Li Peng, Zhu Rongji,
Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Li Lanqing, and 600 Party organization
officials from across the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
