<HEADLINE> China's Machinery Industry Showing Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Minister of
Machine-Building Industry Bao Xuding told a national conference
here today that major economic indicators show an upturn in spite
of difficulties and that the machine-building industry had stable
growth this year with 490 billion yuan in output value, a
year-on-year increase of 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to Bao, the industry expects to have 460 billion yuan
in sales this year, up 5 percent over last year, and 123 billion
yuan in industrial added value, a rise of 6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Electronics and machinery exports are expected to exceed 55
billion US dollars worth this year, and out of ten major sectors,
engineering machinery, automobiles, and instruments and meters had
big increases, but the machine tool sector still reported negative
growth.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Machine-Building Industry focused on improving
product quality, a better organization structure, and building
research and development ability, Bao said. The Ministry will
increase its understanding of ownership structure, industrial
organization structure, and changes in the growth and management
mode, and will make every effort to hone its competitive edge on
the international market.
</P>
<P>
The China First Auto Works Group, Dongfeng Automotive Group,
and Shanghai Automotive Industry Group will take the lead in
reorganization, and large auto groups with annual sales of 40
billion yuan, fixed assets of 5 billion yuan, and good product
development and sales will be formed.
</P>
<P>
Large enterprise groups of petrochemical equipment, project
machinery, farm machinery, and machine tools are expected to be
set up after capital reorganization in the hope that they can help
change the unconcentrated and unsystematic state of the machinery
industry.
</P>
<P>
Total industrial output for 1998 is estimated at 540 billion
yuan, up 7 percent over 1997, and industrial added value, 130
billion yuan, up 5.7 percent.  
</P>
