<HEADLINE> Chechen Fighters Attack Russian Tank Battalion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Chechen fighters attacked the
city of Buynaksk in the southern Russian republic of Dagestan
early Monday morning, causing several casualties, burning four
tanks and vehicles and taking nine hostages away to Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Russian media reported that about 30 fighters armed with
machine-guns and rocket-launchers attacked a Russian tank
battalion stationed in Buynaksk.
</P>
<P>
During the two-hour volley of gunfire, two tanks, two fuel
trucks and three military trucks were burned down. One civilian
was killed and five people injured.
</P>
<P>
The fighters then took five policemen and four soliders as
hostages and escaped to Chechnya. On the way of escape, they
kidnaped a passenger bus with many passengers on board.
</P>
<P>
The gang were reportedly surrounded by police and troops in the
Kazbek area of Dagestan around 1.5 kilometers from the Chechen
border. Two of the fighters were captured in the process.
</P>
<P>
However, the Chechens managed to sneak across the border into
Chechnya where they released most of the hostages, but still
keeping nine in hand.
</P>
<P>
Commander of the North Caucasian Military District Victor
Kazantsev has flown to the troubled area to cope with the
aftermath of the attack. 
</P>
