<HEADLINE> 3 Iranian Mountaineers Killed in Avalanche </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The frozen bodies of three
mountaineers killed in an avalanche five days ago was found today
in Iran's western province of Hamadan.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency IRNA said that the
mountaineers were attacked by an avalanche while climbing the
Mount Alvand. Rescue operations started soon after the three
mountaineers were announced missing.
</P>
<P>
The bodies were pulled out of snow on a height known as Kalagh
Laneh, the report said, adding that one of the victims was a
veteran mountaineer.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers reported today that another young mountaineer
was rescued by relief team on the mountain north of the capital
city of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The mountaineer fell into a snow-covered valley of 140 meters
deep on Friday and was dragged out 57 hours later. 
</P>
