<HEADLINE> Jones Banned for Three Months for Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Dean Jones of Barnsley was
banned for three months as he became the first player to fail a
drug test with an English premier league club, the Football
Association said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old defender, who has to play for the first team,
tested positive for amphetamines at a random training-ground test
on October 27.
</P>
<P>
He was charged with misconduct by the Football Association and
suspended after failing the test.
</P>
<P>
Jones pleaded guilty to the offence at a hearing in London,
saying he took the drug at a nightclub, and was warned a life ban
for any further doping offence. 
</P>
