<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Gives Details Of How To Keep Officials Clean and Honest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Central Commission for
Discipline Inspection of the Communist Party of China (CPC) is
re-emphasizing the need for Party members and leading officials to
be clean and honest.
</P>
<P>
It supplied more details on September 3 to supplement the
guidelines, which Xinhua released today. These detailed rules,
which are in three chapters and 38 articles, explain the
prohibition on abuse of power by Party members and leading
officials in administrative, judicial, and discipline inspection
departments.
</P>
<P>
Party members and leading officials can not run businesses that
are individually funded or share-issuing and co-operative, and can
not lease businesses or take part-time jobs.
</P>
<P>
Party members and leading officials are warned about
appropriating public funds or paying personal expenses with public
funds, taking advantage of their power.
</P>
<P>
Officials are prohibited from seeking personal gain in the
process of selecting or appointing cadres and can not benefit
their families or relatives by means of their power or influence.
</P>
<P>
They are also cautioned about extravagance and wasting of
public money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
