<HEADLINE> Hungarian PM Confident of Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The most difficult period for
the Hungarian economy is over, Prime Minister Horn Gyula told
the press on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Economic growth has begun, foreign debts have drastically
fallen and budget deficit has been brought under control, Horn
said.
</P>
<P>
Industrial productivity increased by 10 percent, Horn said,
adding that all-round privatization has laid a foundation for
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The government will continue its current political and economic
policies in the near future, with an annual 5 percent reduction in
inflation rate being the top priority, he said.
</P>
<P>
Other pressing tasks include reforming the medical insurance
and social welfare systems, improving public security and
promoting equal opportunities for all in education, Horn added.
</P>
