<HEADLINE> Auditing Important in Developing Market Economy: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng has
called for increased supervision by auditors across China to check
embezzlement and other economic crimes.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the remark when meeting representatives to a
national conference on auditing here today.
</P>
<P>
China is in the process of establishing a socialist market
economy, Li told the representatives. "With legislation far from
being perfect, some people have seized loopholes in the legal
system to embezzle state assets or take bribery."
</P>
<P>
He hoped that Party committees and governments at all levels
will understand the importance of auditing, and enhance leadership
over the auditing work.
</P>
<P>
The premier expressed his appreciation for the work done by
auditors throughout the country, which has saved the state more
than 30 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
"More important, supervision by auditors has played a positive
role in maintaining the country's financial and economic order,
promoting the campaign for a cleaner government, and guaranteeing
a healthy development of the national economy," the premier
stressed.
</P>
<P>
He urged auditing departments to further carry out the Auditing
Law and the detailed rules to execute the law, and to improve the
supervision mechanism. 
</P>
