<HEADLINE> Leading Travel Agencies Jointly Promoting Outbound FIT Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Nine Beijing-based Chinese
travel agencies are joining hands to promote the "Royal Orchid
Holiday" tour to Thailand when Chinese people are preparing for
traveling abroad at the New Year and Spring Festival holidays.
</P>
<P>
The first cooperation of the travel businesses in selling
outbound tours, the move is designed not only to provide a new
choice for travelers, but also to combat unauthorized outbound
tour operations which are becoming rampant, according to Li Lu'an,
President of China Travel Agency Association and General Manager
of the Head Office of China International Travel Service.
</P>
<P>
Chinese government has authorized 67 travel agencies across the
country to sell outbound tours, of which 11 are based in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
However, dozens of illegal operators have been seen in Beijing
offering outbound tours, many of which are characterized in
low-price and low-quality. According to China National Tourism
Administration, over 80 percent of the complaints resulted from
such tours.
</P>
<P>
"Royal Orchid Holiday", a 25-year-old world-famous tour jointly
run by Thai Airways and Thai travel agencies, is a low-priced,
high-quality FIT (foreign individual tourist) tour featuring
colorful sightseeing, five-star hotel accommodation, and
no-shopping arrangement.
</P>
<P>
Chinese participants of the tour, who should hold a five-year
passport for private affairs, can decide the departure time
themselves, and the travel agencies can arrange the tour for them
in about a week after their application is filed.
</P>
<P>
"The fall of group tours and the rise of FIT tours represent
a trend of the international travel industry. Though China's
outbound market still lacks mature FIT product, the demand on FIT
tours will gradually grow," said a travel agent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
