<HEADLINE> Largest Securities Broker in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The largest securities broker
in northeast China was established as the result of a
restructuring move which separated the Liaoning Provincial
Securities Co. from the Provincial Branch of the People's Bank of
China, the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The new broker, a limited-liability company, involves a total
investment of 254 million yuan provided by 25 institutional
shareholders.
</P>
<P>
The shareholders include nine local securities firms which were
previously attached to PBC's Liaoning branch. The new company,
which has 19 subsidiaries, is qualified to offer wide-ranging
securities transactions.
</P>
<P>
The PBC branch established the former company with an
investment of 10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local economists note that the restructuring came in response
to the changing situation involving increasing enterprise mergers
and acquisitions, and will benefit the efforts of state-owned
enterprises to raise funds on the capital market. 
</P>
