<HEADLINE> Philippine Trade Deficit Narrows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' trade deficit
in the first 10 months of the year narrowed down by 8.6 percent to
9.312 billion U.S. dollars from 10.187 billion dollars during the
same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
However, trade deficit for October alone represented a 4.0
percent increase to 1.014 billion dollars from 975 million dollars
last year, the National Statistics Office said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Data released from the office showed that total trade for the
first 10 months grew by 15.7 percent to 50.689 billion dollars
from 43.807 billion dollars a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Payments for imported goods went up 11.1 percent to 30.001
billion dollars from 26.997 billion dollars while receipts from
exports increased by 23.1 percent to 20.689 billion dollars from
16.810 billion dollars, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
Aggregate trade value for October stood at 5.566 billion
dollars, 19.5 percent higher than 4.743 billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
