<HEADLINE> Effective Supervision of Financial Markets Needed: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Noted non-resident Indian
industrialist Lord Swraj Paul Monday called for more effective
supervision of Indian financial markets, banking and investment
systems.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a conference of non-resident Indians (NRIs) here, he
said that there was an important message for this country in the
economic crisis that had engulfed several nations in Southeast
Asia. The more open an economy is, the more there is need for
tough regulatory measures. Effective supervision was essential if
successful inward investment flows were to be sustained.
</P>
<P>
Referring to India's economic reforms since 1991, he said that
the agenda of economic reforms had moved forward in the last seven
years.
</P>
<P>
However, he warned of a trap that often besets reformers -- the
risk of abandoning reforms along the way or pursuing them
half-heartedly. Tentative reform is a greater danger than no
reform.  
</P>
