<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Foreign Reserves Hit 96.5 Bln US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The latest figure represented a 5.6-percent increase over that
of a month earlier, when Hong Kong's foreign reserves stood at
91.4 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Joseph Yam, chief executive of the HKMA, said Monday that
the rise in foreign reserves showed that there were inflows of
money into Hong Kong despite the Asian financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
