of the higher interest rates, jacked up in late October to fend
off speculative attacks, said Yam.
</P>
<P>
At the end of November, the foreign reserves vested in the
Exchange Fund were 79.1 billion U.S. dollars, while those held in
the Land Fund were 17.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong remains the world's third largest foreign reserves
holder, after Japan and Chinese mainland.  
