<HEADLINE> Macao Curriculum Hotline Popular Among Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- A special hotline offering help
for students in their homework has turned out to be particularly
popular among primary students in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Between January and October this year, more than 50,000
students phoned in to ask for instructions with their homework.
Currently, about 300 students call each day, compared with about
200 phone calls last June, organizers told the Macao Daily News
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Most of the calls seek help on questions in the Chinese course,
math and English, and most of the callers are fifth and sixth
graders at primary schools.
</P>
<P>
Jointly launched by the Youth Division of the Education and
Youth Department of Macao and the Chinese Students Association
last year, the hotline is available to students between 17:00 and
22:00 on weekdays.
</P>
<P>
Due to increasing popularity, organizers have increased the
number of people answering phones from eight last year to 14 this
year, and the number of telephone lines has increased to
eight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
