<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Honored European Player of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian superstar Ronaldo has
been named the European Player of the Year by overwhelming flocks
of votes organized by the France-Football magazine.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old soccer genius, who moved from Spanish Barcelona
to Italian Inter Milan for a world record 30 million dollars in
the close-season, was the first Brazilian and youngest player to
win the award.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo collected 222 votes, beating Real Madrid's Yugoslav
striker Predrag Mijatovic by 150 votes, while French midfielder
Zinedine Zidane, who plays for Italian Juventus, was third.
</P>
<P>
German international defender Matthias Sammer of the European
Cup champions Borussia Dortmund was last year's winner of the
European Player.
</P>
<P>
The award was opened to non-Europeans playing in Europe two
year ago. 
