<HEADLINE> 1 Million US Dollars Worth of Jewelry Stolen in Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Thieves stole 1.17 million US
dollars worth of gold and diamond jewelry from a central Sydney
hotel room after kicking down the door while the owner was out,
police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Four black display suitcases containing 900 pieces of gold and
diamond jewelry were stolen from the room of a Spanish wholesaler
visiting jewelers in Sydney on August 26.
</P>
<P>
The designs of the stolen goods were very distinctive and the
entire collection was the work of highly skilled craftsmen which
would be easily recognizable by experienced jewelers, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police, who have released details in the hope that someone
might come forward, are seeking a fat man in his 40s, of olive
complexion and with dark, collar-length, thinning hair.
</P>
<P>
The man was last seen in the lobby of the hotel talking in
Spanish to two smaller companions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
