<DOCNO> XIE19971222.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao's Exports to U.S. Increase 26 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Macao's exports to the United
States in the first nine months of the year surged 26 percent
from the same period last year, the Macao Daily News reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The leading importer for Macao, the United States bought 5.576
billion patacas (about 697 million US dollars) worth of goods from
Macao during that period, up 26 percent.
</P>
<P>
Most of the exports to the U.S. like knitwear increased more
than 20 percent. Exports of leather shoes, office equipment and
computer products also increased. But exports of garments,
furniture and porcelain products dropped.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Macao bought three percent less products from the
U.S. in the January-September period. The imports of raw
materials, semi-finished goods and fuel declined between 15
percent to 30 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the Macao Trade and Investment Promotion
Bureau received a total of 591 inquiries between January and
November, involving both imports and exports of such products as
garments, electronics, medicine and foodstuff.
</P>
<P>
Most of the inquiries came from Asia, followed by those from
Europe, Africa and North America.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
