<HEADLINE> Over 926 Kg of Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 926.69 kilograms
(kg) of narcotic drugs, including 356 kg of opium and 89 kg of
heroin, were seized by the Myanmar authorities in the country from
December 1 to 15, according to an official Information Sheet
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, made by the anti-narcotic task force in various
states and divisions, also included 2,046,552 tablets of
Methamphetamine (stimulant drug), the Information Sheet added.
</P>
<P>
In November, the Myanmar authorities confiscated 1,213 kg of
narcotic drugs including 394 kg of heroin in the country,
according to an earlier official report.  
</P>
