<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Speeds up Anti-smuggling Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam detected 1,400 cases of
smuggling and trade fraudulence, and handled illegal imports worth
62 billion vietnamese dong ( 4.7 million U.S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
These were achieved over one month of implementation of the
national anti-smuggling and trade fraudulence campaign.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam News Agency Monday said in a report that smuggling and
trade fraudulence has increased in vietnam in recent years.
</P>
<P>
It added that about 4-5 percent of retail sales revenue in 1997
was from illegal imports, resulting in tax losses of 10,000
billion dong (769 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
At present Vietnam is taking measures to prevent smuggling and
trade fraudulence, including affixing tax stamps to three imported
goods: bicycles, electric fans, and foreign alcohol.
</P>
<P>
Since Decembr 1, all the three kinds of imports whether stored
in warehouses, kept in shops or delivered are regarded as smuggled
goods if they do not display the proper import duty stamps. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
