<HEADLINE> Iran, Iraq Exchange Bodies of Dead Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Iraq this morning
exchanged bodies of seven Iranian and 37 Iraqi soldiers killed
during the Iran-Iraq war (1980-88).
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA said that the bodies were
swapped at the Shalamcheh border point in Iran's southwestern
province of Khuzestan.
</P>
<P>
Head of Iran's armed forces committee in charge of searching
for those missing in action General Mirfaisal Baqerzadeh and his
Iraqi counterpart attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The two officials also discussed ways of speeding up search
operations, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of Iranian and Iraqi soldiers were
killed in the eight-year bloody war, while several thousand are
still listed as missing. During the past years, the two countries
have exchanged hundreds of bodies.
</P>
<P>
Tehran and Baghdad have announced their readiness to solve
remaining issues between them, including the problems of
prisoners of war (POW), in order to improve bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Iran released 500 Iraqi POWs in a bid to encourage
Baghdad to follow suit. In return, Iraq freed two Iranians
arrested shortly after the Gulf War in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971222.0112 </DOCNO>
