<HEADLINE> 1,000-Year-Old Government Office in China Open to Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- China has successfully
renovated a 1000-year-old government building in north China's
Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The Huozhou Ancient Government Office, the best protected one
in China, is in the center of Huozhou City. It was designated as
one of the key cultural relics under the State protection last
November.
</P>
<P>
Weathering 1,000 years of wind and rain, the old building
looked shabby and some of the paintings on the walls could hardly
been seen. The central and provincial governments have
earmarked 340,000 yuan (about 42,500 US dollars) for its
renovation and protection.
</P>
<P>
The ancient office is now open to public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
