<HEADLINE> Commissioner's Office Supports HKSAR in Handling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The commissioner of the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR) said his office has given full support to the
HKSAR in conducting on its own the external affairs authorized by
the Central People's Government.
</P>
<P>
Over the past six months, the office of the commissioner has
tried its best to protect, in accordance with the Basic Law, the
legitimate rights and interests of Hong Kong people residing
abroad, Commissioner Ma Yuzhen said in a recent interview with
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that his office will make further efforts to promote
Hong Kong's relations with foreign countries and better safeguard
the legitimate rights and interests of Hong Kong people residing
abroad.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with Articles 13, 149 and 151 of the Basic Law,
he noted, the HKSAR government enjoys extensive authorization from
the Central People's Government to deal with external affairs.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment, he said, the commissioner's office has
acted strictly in accordance with the Basic Law by offering
support and assistance to the HKSAR government in those external
affairs within authorization. The handling of specific matters
rests entirely with the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
Over the past six months, he said, the office of the
commissioner, under the leadership of the Central People's
Government and the Foreign Ministry, has assisted representatives
of the HKSAR government in attending nearly 30 international
conferences as members of Chinese government delegations. It has
conveyed to the HKSAR government a number of instruments from the
Central People's Government authorizing the HKSAR government to
negotiate with more than 30 countries for over 40 bilateral
agreements covering six areas.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner's office has given the HKSAR government a list
of more than 200 international treaties applicable to Hong Kong
and helped it solve the legal issues arising from relevant
international rights and obligations, and implement 11 resolutions
on sanctions adopted by the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Ma said his office also helped the HKSAR government make
preparations for the Annual Conference of the World Bank and the
International Monetary Fund held in Hong Kong last September.
</P>
</TEXT>
