<HEADLINE> Uganda-Kenya Highway Reopened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda-Kenya highway,
which was damaged by floods, has been reopened after intensive
repairs, The Monitor paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The traffic became normal just by 01:00 p.m. Sunday,
said Robert Kibuuka, an engineer of the Ministry of Works,
Transport and Communications.
</P>
<P>
The ministry fixed the road in Walugogo valley where heavy
rains created a four-meter trench in the highway.
</P>
<P>
Walugogo valley is a strategic passage point just east of
Iganga town linking not only the east and the northeast with
Kampala, but is also the only traffic point linking central
Africa and east Africa.
</P>
<P>
John Nasasira, the Minister of Works, Transport and
Communications, sponsored the repairing on the scene, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
