<HEADLINE> Shanghai Zoo Adds 4,000 New Members of Animal Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Zoo this year
witnessed the increase of nearly 4,000 newly-born animals or newly
introduced animals from foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Shanghai Zoo has over 14,000 animals of 596 kinds,
15 kinds more than a year before.
</P>
<P>
Starting from the beginning of 1997, 35 kinds of beasts and 38
kinds of birds gave birth to their children. Of the newly-born
animals, 41 are rare animals enjoying state protection.
</P>
<P>
Workers from the zoo said it is the first time in China that
white-hipped entellus monkeys in the zoo have their babies.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, Shanghai Zoo has introduced more than
2,700 animals of 131 varieties from other countries.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Zoo spends every year 2.4 million yuan (280,000 US
dollars) on purchasing animal fodder.
</P>
<P>
To improve the animals life quality, the zoo spent 2.7 million
yuan (320,000 dollars) to upgrade the animal houses to imitate the
natural ecological environment. 
</P>
