<HEADLINE> 900,000 Farmers in Central China Province Shake Off Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan
province has succeeded in reducing the poverty-stricken
population from 3.5 million last year to the present 2.6 million.
</P>
<P>
The province has 31 impoverished counties, which are mainly
distributed in the mountainous areas with harsh natural
conditions.
</P>
<P>
This year, the province has raised 980 million yuan (122.5
million US dollars) from all the sectors to aid the poor, an
increase of 71.6 percent on last year.
</P>
<P>
With the money, the 31 poor counties have turned over 13,000
hectares of dry land into paddy fields and built power facilities
for 39,000 farmers, drinking water projects for 565,000 farmers,
and 6,100 kilometers of roads.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has sent some 11,000 officals at
various levels to 3,500 poor villages to help farmers develop
economy.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the per-capita income in these villages has
increase to 670 yuan (83.7 US dollars) this year from 470 yuan
last year.
</P>
<P>
And the per-capita grain output has reached 360 kilograms this
year, 80 kilograms more than last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the 31 counties have realized more than
two billion yuan of revenue this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
