<HEADLINE> Vietnam Earns 530 Million Dollars From Tourism This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's tourism sector has
earned 7,000 billion dong (about 538 million U.S. dollars) this
year, up more than 14 percent over 1996, the local newspaper,
Vietnam Tourism Industry, reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, about 1.7 million overseas visitors
have been to Vietnam this year, up 8 percent over 1996, while
domestic holiday-makers numbered 8.5 million, an increase of 30
percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese tourism administration, in collaboration with
related local departments and services, has made improvements to
key tourist centers in three regions of the country and organized
many tourism projects in 13 provinces and cities to promote
tourism.
</P>
<P>
The tourism service has so far had 78 international and 251
national travel businesses, which have signed hundreds of tourism
contracts with foreign travel companies.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has also promoted visits made by Chinese tourists
to Hanoi through the three Sino-Vietnamese border gates by
allowing them to use pass permits only.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam now has 3,050 hotels with a total of 50,000 rooms
including 28,000 rooms of international standard and 260 star
hotels. The country is expected to attract 1.9 million overseas
visitors and about 11 million domestic tourists next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
