<HEADLINE> World Bank Projects Doing Well In Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 22 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has just been granted 260 million US dollars in loans
from the World Bank for its infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
The latest loan will be used in such projects as urban and
rural water supply, environmental protection, afforestation in
poor areas, and animal husbandry, a provincial government official
said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province's capital city of Shijiazhuang is
expected to use 100-million yuan of the World Bank loans in 1998,
on communications.
</P>
<P>
Hebei began to make use of the World Bank loans in 1984. By now
it has received 400 million US dollars, involving 27 projects, 17
of which have been completed.
</P>
<P>
The province has established good reputation with the World
Bank by setting up a reserve funds system to repay the loans in
time. As a result, the Bank has increased its funding to Hebei.
</P>
<P>
With improved investment environment, the province has become
one of the country's major users for government loans as well as
those from international financial organizations.
</P>
<P>
To date, Hebei has completed the construction of 181 projects,
using foreign loans worth 1.5 billion US dollars, accounting for
nearly 30 percent of the province's total foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
During the 1996-2000 period, the province plans to use 3.5
billion US dollars of foreign loans. It has selected more than 60
projects with feasibility studies already completed, the official
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
