<HEADLINE> East China Province Uses WB Loans to Build Pumping Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu province
has utilized a World Bank loan equivalent to 350 million yuan in
the construction and renovation of four large pumping stations.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the completion of the projects has raised the
province's ability of pumping water from the Yangtze River to the
areas north of the Huaihe River.
</P>
<P>
To achieve comprehensive development in agricuture, the
provincial government has decided to build two pumping stations
and renovate two old ones.
</P>
<P>
Government sources said the 13 pumps in the four pumping
stations have a designed flow capacity of 337 cubic meters per
second and they can drain 200 cubic meters of flood per second.
</P>
<P>
During a drought this year, the four pumping stations pumped
one billion cubic meters of water from the Yangtze and Huaihe
rivers, meeting the needs for irrigation, industrial development
and people's life.
</P>
