<HEADLINE> Jilin Drafts Agricultural Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Jilin, a major agricultural
province in northeast China, has drafted regulations governing the
comprehensive management of agricultural resources, according to
the agricultural economic committee under the provincial people's
congress.
</P>
<P>
As one of China's major bread baskets, Jilin is threatened by
dwindling arable land and water resources in a period when many
local governments sacrifice agricultural resources for faster
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The regulations provide for standard farmland investigation,
exploitation, protection and legal responsibilities held for
harming the overall and long-term benefits with regard to the
protection of agricultural resources.
</P>
<P>
Experts here believe that the regulations will serve as
guarantee to ensure sustainable agricultural development, and
enhance the awareness for the comprehensive use of agricultural
resources.  
</P>
