<HEADLINE> Thailand, Australia to Revamp Aviation Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Australia have
agreed in principle to seek a new aviation pact which will have
more fair provisions to both sides, a senior Thai official said.
</P>
<P>
Aviation officials from both countries met here recently and
agreed to revise the current aviation pact, in which Thailand is
at a disadvantage, said Sawat Sitthiwong, director-general of the
Aviation Department of Thailand.
