<HEADLINE> Tianjin Develops Earthquake Reporting System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- A new system which
automatically reports earthquakes within five minutes of their
occurrence has entered operations in north China's Tianjin
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The system, developed by Tianjin Municipal Seismological
Bureau, quickly reports the magnitude, time, and location of
earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, the system not only shortens the
reporting time, but also combines information including rapid
reports, judgements on earthquake development trends, reports on
advanced warning signs, analysis on abnormal phenomena and related
consultations.
</P>
<P>
China's mainland is entering the fifth active seismological
period this century.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has established four seismological stations and four
observation offices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
