<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Introduces New Tour Itineraries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province recently opened a series of new tour itineraries as
part of China's urban and rural tourism activities for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan province is home to abundant tourism resources,
including the Leshan Buddha and the Mt. Ermei. Years of
development has elevated the province's tourism sector to the
position as a pillar industry.
</P>
<P>
The new tour routes include Jiuzhaigou-Huanglong,
Leshan Buddha-Mt Ermei-Dujiangyan-Qingchenshan, and a special
tour to the natural habitat of the Giant Panda.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan's tourism is feathered by a number of activities
reflecting ancient folk culture and the colorful life of the
modern people living in southwest China. These activities include
the Zigong International Lanterns Festival, the Leshan
International Buddha Festival and the Chengdu Flowers Festival.
</P>
<P>
As part of an effort to further develop tourism, the provincial
government and neighboring provinces will jointly open various
regional tour routes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
