<HEADLINE> Chinese Province's Basic Industries Make Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
made remarkable achievements in the development of its basic
industries in recent years.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released by the Anhui provincial
government, the installed generating capacity of the province is
now 7.39 million kw, up 58 percent on 1992.
</P>
<P>
The output of state-run coal mines in the province has climbed
to 40.66 million tons in 1997 and that of local coal mines reached
12.56 million tons, respectively 51-percent and 224-percent
increases compared with 1992.
</P>
<P>
The installed capacity of program-controlled switchboards has
grown by 2.8 million lines this year, a 7.52-fold increase on
1992. And, its highway mileage has reached 37,200 km, a
21.6 percent increase.
</P>
