<HEADLINE> Bulgarian PM Describes 1997 as Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan
Kostov has described the year of 1997 as a dramatic and successful
one for his government in which Bulgaria restored its dignity.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Bulgarian Telegraph Agency Sunday,
Kostov said under the government's policies, a series of tough
problems have been resolved, and the country has started to pull
through the first stage of its economic crisis.
</P>
