<HEADLINE> China's Largest Shipbuilding Center Recuperates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Amid hails, a 10,000-dwt barge
was recently launched from the platform of the Dongfu Shipbuilding
Industrial Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The vessel, 98 meters long, 25 meters wide and nine meters
hight, is the largest ever turned out by Fu'an city in Fujian
province, east China.
</P>
<P>
Xu Guichun, an official in Fu'an City, said the shipbuilding
industry in the city has resumed its past glory as one of the
country's largest maintenance center for privately owned ships.
</P>
<P>
The shipbuilding industry in Fu'an became bleak in 1995,
because of overdue expansion and poor quality control.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, Fu'an has begun to take measures to recuperate
its shipbuilding industry. It reduced the number of shipyards to 40
from 300 and started building new ships.
</P>
<P>
The output value of Fu'an shipbuilding industry is expected to
reach 380 million yuan this year. And the figure will be 600
million yuan next year.
</P>
<P>
The Dongfu company is now the major ship manufacturer in Fu'an
with its 50 million yuan in output value. Chen Ping, general
manager of the company, said the city is intending to form a large
group company in the sector.  
</P>
</TEXT>
