<HEADLINE> Pudong Records Foreign Trade Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The import and export volume
for Shanghai's Pudong New Area totalled 8.6 billion U.S. dollars
for the first 11 months of this year, up 25 percent on last year's
same period.
</P>
<P>
The annual trade volume for the flourishing economic center is
expected to top nine billion U.S. dollars, according to a local
trade official.
</P>
<P>
The processing industry accounted for 38 percent of the total
trade volume, with the sector's rapid growth attributed, at least
in part, to preferential treatment by the government.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises recorded a foreign trade volume of
3.9 billion US dollars, or 45 percent of the area's total trade
volume.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's major imports include computers, integrated circuits
and micro-electronic spare parts, with major exports including
machinery, electronic products, garments and woven products.
</P>
<P>
Japan is Pudong's largest trade partner, followed by the
United States and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
