<HEADLINE> Beijing to Build More Theatres </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will construct more
theatres in the next two years to meet the increasing demand of
its residents, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
China National Theatre is on the construction list, and it is
to be built to the west of the Great Hall of the People. Upon
completion, the theatre will be the largest of its kind in the
country.
</P>
<P>
A nationwide contest, now in its closing stages, has been held
to choose the best design for it.
</P>
<P>
The theatre, covering 3.67 hectares, will have a total
construction area of 100,000-120,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Construction will start in the first half of next year and the
main part of the building is due to be completed in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Sources said early in 1958, designs were made for the theatre
but its construction was deferred, mainly due to shortages of
funds.
</P>
<P>
Besides this theatre, the capital is to build the planned
800-seat Chinese Pingju Opera Theatre, the Capital Library as well
as museums in the next two years to enrich the cultural life of
Beijingers.  
</P>
