<HEADLINE> Shanghai Boosts Information Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Booming information
infrastructure construction has played an important role in
economic development in Shanghai, China's largest manufacturing
city.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's optical fiber network radiates in all directions and
currently stretches 6,000 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The handling capacity of the city's computerized telephone
switching system stands at 5.2 million lines.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has formed the world's largest cable TV network which
offers two million subscribers with diversified colorful
programming on 46 channels.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has installed a variety of computer networks in
various departments, including the Municipal Government, banks,
customs and the transportation system, as well as a
high-efficiency network available for digital transmissions and TV
conferences.
</P>
<P>
Industry insiders note that the construction of information
infrastructure is an important step to enable Shanghai to realize
its goal of becoming a vital international information center by
the year 2010.  
</P>
</TEXT>
