<HEADLINE> Brazil Wins Confederations' Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's striking duo Ronaldo
and Romario scored a hat-trick apiece as Brazil crushed 10-man
Australia 6-0 to win the Confederations' Cup here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The game was degenerated into a one-sided exhibition in the
24th minute when Australian striker Mark Viduka was sent off for a
wild challenge on Brazil wingback Cafu.
</P>
<P>
By then Brazil were already overwhelming after an explosive
start that saw Australian goalkeeper Mark Bosnich make four good
saves in the opening 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The inevitable breakthrough came in the 15th minute when
Denilson waltzed to the byline and cut back the ball for the
unmarked Ronaldo to hit into the top of the net.
</P>
<P>
The Inter Milan star striked for the second in the 28th minute
as he stole between two defenders and tapped the ball past Bosnich
into the net to make it 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Seven minutes before the half time, the 1994 World Cup winner
Romario made it three as he rushed down the right flank and hit
home.
</P>
<P>
After 75 minutes it was 6-0 as Ronaldo completed his hat-trick
in the 59th minute and Romario's two second-half goals in the 53rd
and a penalty spot shot in the 75th minutes.
</P>
<P>
The six-goal triumph came just a week after Australia had held
the Brazilians to a goalless draw in a group match at the same
venue.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Sunday the Czech Republic beat Uruguay 1-0 in the
third place play-off match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
