<HEADLINE> Installed Generating Capacity Increases in Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The installed generating
capacity in east China's Shandong Province had reached 16
million KW by middle December, 1.8 million KW more than
last year.
</P>
<P>
According to Liu Zhenya, general manager of the Shangdong
Electricity Group, an average of 1.5 million KW were added each
year to the province's installed capacity over recent years,
greatly reducing power shortages.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that the province's total power production this year
is expected to hit 84 billion KWH, 4.7 billion KWH more than last
year.
</P>
<P>
Shandong now ranks second in China in both installed generating
capacity and power production. 
</P>
