<HEADLINE> Mubarak Holds Talks with Gabonese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
today discussed with President Omar Bongo of Gabon African
issues of common concern, developments of the Mideast peace
process and promoting bilateral economic ties.
</P>
<P>
Bongo arrived here today for a three-day visit to promote
economic relations with Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Ministers of Egypt and Gabon also discussed their economic
relations and preparation for further official talks Monday,
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa told reporters following the
talks.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to resume meetings of the Joint
Egyptian-Gabonese Committee with the participation of the private
sector and cooperation between businessmen and chambers of
commerce in the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
This is aimed at boosting economic ties, stepping up the volume
of trade exchange which is still modest, and opening markets for
products of the two countries, besides investing in joint ventures
and setting up a bank to finance joint projects, Moussa added.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Gabon are expected to sign Monday five agreements on
bilateral cooperation in the domains of economy, health, science
and technology, investment protection, and avoiding double
taxation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bongo and his spouse are accompanied during the visit by the
ministers of foreign affairs, public works, oil, mining and
tourism. 
</P>
