<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-21 21:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Suspends Death Sentence for Jordanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has informed Jordan it has
suspended a death sentence for a Jordanian prisoner, a move aimed
at easing the tension caused by its execution of five Jordanians
this month, Jordan's official news agency, Petra, reported today.
</P>
<P>
The suspension of the death sentence for the prisoner Ammar
Ghaleb Shebabeddine charged with smuggling car spare parts is a
result of continuous contacts between the two countries, Jordanian
Foreign Minister Fayez Tarawneh told Petra.
</P>
<P>
Tarawneh said that Jordan has tried its best to ensure fair
trial for every Jordanian prisoner by Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Official estimates have put the number of Jordanian prisoners
in Iraq at more than 100. But according to unofficial sources,
Iraq holds more than 600 Jordanian prisoners.
</P>
<P>
The suspension of death sentence for Shebabeddine came amid
reports that Jordan and Iraq would take steps to strengthen
economic cooperation in the coming weeks.
</P>
<P>
Petra today quoted an anonymous Jordanian official as saying
that an Iraqi delegation will arrive in Amman to sign a commercial
agreement aimed to expand bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has intended to increase its imports of badly needed food
and medicine through Jordan's port of Aqaba.
</P>
<P>
It also wants to increase imports of Jordanian goods from 255
million U.S. dollars in 1997 to 300 million dollars in 1998, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Jordan has asked Iraq to export more oil to it, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq executed five Jordanians on charge of smuggling car spare
parts and murder earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
And Jordan expelled seven Iraqi diplomats in retaliation and
expressed perplexity with Iraq's actions.
</P>
<P>
Jordan sided with Iraq during the 1990 Gulf crisis caused by
Iraqi invasion of Kuwait. After the Gulf War in 1991 that drove
the Iraqi troops out of Kuwait, the bilateral ties suffered a
setback as Jordan distanced itself from Iraq to end international
alienation.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the ties have been picking up as Iraq begins
to provide the kingdom with more and more oil at discount prices
and keeps increasing imports from Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Iraq exported to Jordan 625 million dollars worth of oil this
year, a 7 percent increase over the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
