<HEADLINE> Scottish Parliament Poll Date Fixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
London, December 21 (Xinhua) - The first election for
Scotland's new devolved parliament will take place on May 6, 1999,
the British government announced today.
</P>
<P>
The historic vote will be the first time that proportional
representation will be used for an election on the British
mainland.
</P>
<P>
The vote will be combined with the Scottish local government
elections and the new parliament, the first in Scotland for 300
years, will be running by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The new parliament will meet in Edinburgh. Its 129 members will
have wide powers including the right to raise taxes.
</P>
<P>
The Labor government's plan for a Scottish parliament was
approved in a referendum in September by a big majority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
